notes.body: Hello Prateek,     Greetings from PharmEasy!     This email is with reference to the concern raised for order #654435868403802112-62786.     We have received an update from our logistics team. As per the update, your order has been delivered to you. Please accept my sincere apology for the inconvenience caused to you. We have shared the required feedback with the delivery agent and we will make sure that such instances are not repeated in the future.     Please consider this as a one-off instance as we aim to provide the best of services to our customers and such instances are very rare.     Since you are a valued customer, as a token of apology, we have credited Rs.30/- to your PharmEasy wallet on 03 December 2025.     We are marking the ticket as resolved. PharmEasy looks forward to bettering your experience in the future.     For any further assistance, please reopen this ticket or reach out to us through our support channels, in the App or website, listed in the 'Need Help' section.      Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!     Regards,   PharmEasy
notes.body_html:
Hello Prateek,

Greetings from PharmEasy!
 
This email is with reference to the concern raised for order #654435868403802112-62786.
 
We have received an update from our logistics team. As per the update, your order has been delivered to you. Please accept my sincere apology for the inconvenience caused to you. We have shared the required feedback with the delivery agent and we will make sure that such instances are not repeated in the future.
 
Please consider this as a one-off instance as we aim to provide the best of services to our customers and such instances are very rare.

Since you are a valued customer, as a token of apology, we have credited Rs.30/- to your PharmEasy wallet on 03 December 2025.

We are marking the ticket as resolved. PharmEasy looks forward to bettering your experience in the future.

For any further assistance, please reopen this ticket or reach out to us through our support channels, in the App or website, listed in the 'Need Help' section. 
 
Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!

Regards, 
PharmEasy

We have shared the required feedback with the delivery agent and we will make sure that such instances are not repeated in the future.     Also we would like to inform you that cancellation refund of Rs.676.08/- initiated on 30th November 2025 and same will be refunded to your source account within 5-7 business days.     We would request you to place a new order and we will ensure the order is delivered to you on priority.     Be rest assured as we have jotted down the details of your experience and PharmEasy will ensure all appropriate actions are taken to prevent similar situations from happening in the future. notes.body_html:
Hello Ankita Singh,

Greetings from PharmEasy!
 
This email is with reference to the concern raised for order #649344905137811456-90431. 
 
We can see that your order was canceled on 30th November 2025. Due to some unforeseen circumstances, the order was not delivered to you by the expected date of delivery. We apologize for the inconvenience caused to you with your order.

We have shared the required feedback with the delivery agent and we will make sure that such instances are not repeated in the future.
 
Also we would like to inform you that cancellation refund of Rs.676.08/- initiated on 30th November 2025 and same will be refunded to your source account within 5-7 business days.
 
We would request you to place a new order and we will ensure the order is delivered to you on priority.
 
Be rest assured as we have jotted down the details of your experience and PharmEasy will ensure all appropriate actions are taken to prevent similar situations from happening in the future. Looking forward to delighting you soon.
 
If you have any queries, please feel free to get back to us.
 
For any further assistance, please reopen this ticket or reach out to us through our support channels, in the App or website, listed in the 'Need Help' section.
 
Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!
 
Regards,
PharmEasy

notes.body: Hello Abhiram,  Greetings from PharmEasy!     I am sorry to hear that you wish to deactivate your PharmEasy account.    I have forwarded your account deactivation request to our escalations team. Let me inform you that, once the account is deactivated then we cannot process any request or reactivate the account. Once confirmed our team will reach out within 24 to 48 hours to complete the account deactivation process on a registered mobile number to confirm if you requested account deactivation.      If yes, an OTP will be generated and will be sent to your registered mobile number. Once the OTP is shared by you to the team, they will go ahead and block the customer's account.     Please be assured, I have forwarded your request to unsubscribe your number '9762717739' from getting the promotional notifications. It will take 3 working days to process it completely. You will only receive your order-related information.    Further, if you wish to unsubscribe from getting the promotional notifications on your email id too, I request you to open your latest promotional email and hit unsubscribe at the bottom right-hand side corner to stop email promotions.   Your patience and understanding are highly appreciated in the meantime.   Regards,     Neeha
notes.body_html:
Hello Abhiram,

Greetings from PharmEasy!

I am sorry to hear that you wish to deactivate your PharmEasy account. 

I have forwarded your account deactivation request to our escalations team. Let me inform you that, once the account is deactivated then we cannot process any request or reactivate the account. Once confirmed our team will reach out within 24 to 48 hours to complete the account deactivation process on a registered mobile number to confirm if you requested account deactivation. 

If yes, an OTP will be generated and will be sent to your registered mobile number. Once the OTP is shared by you to the team, they will go ahead and block the customer's account.

Please be assured, I have forwarded your request to unsubscribe your number '9762717739' from getting the promotional notifications. It will take 3 working days to process it completely. You will only receive your order-related information. 

Further, if you wish to unsubscribe from getting the promotional notifications on your email id too, I request you to open your latest promotional email and hit unsubscribe at the bottom right-hand side corner to stop email promotions.

Your patience and understanding are highly appreciated in the meantime.

Regards,
Neeha

helpdesk_ticket.description:
To,
The PharmEasy Support,
PharmEasy

Date: December 2, 2025

Dear Sir/Madam,

I am writing to formally express my disappointment and concern regarding
the delivery of my recent order (#653494142074617856), placed on November
29, 2025, for an amount of Rs. 1,372.77.

Today, December 2, 2025, the delivery person (who introduced himself as Mr.
Vijay) not only delivered the order a day later than scheduled but also
demanded Rs. 2,447 instead of the actual order value. To my shock, the
invoice pasted on the parcel appeared tampered, with the amount to reflect
sum.

This is not the first time I have faced issues with deliveries from
PharmEasy. Last month, another order was wrongfully cancelled and displayed
as "cancelled by the customer," which was entirely untrue. These repeated
incidents point to a systemic issue in your delivery process, where
customers are being misled and overcharged.

Such practices are unacceptable and erode trust in your platform. I request
the following actions:

1. An immediate reaction to why the delivery person demanded an excess
amount (Rs. 1,074).
2. A thorough investigation into the conduct of the delivery personnel and
the tampering of invoices.
3. Assurance that such incidents will not recur.

For your kind information, I have enclosed the tampered payment receipt and
invoice.
I expect a prompt resolution and a detailed response within 48 hours.
Please feel free to contact me for any clarification.

I look forward to your prompt attention and action.

Sincerely,
Dr A. Nicholas Daniel

-- 


Disclaimer:

This email contains proprietary, business-confidential, 
and/or privileged material. The information contained in this e-mail is 
intended solely for the use of the individual to whom it is addressed. If 
you are not the intended recipient, you are hereby notified that any 
disclosure, copying, distribution or action in relation to the contents of 
this email is strictly prohibited and may be unlawful and request you to 
permanently delete this message and any attachments herein. You are 
requested to advise the sender, of your receipt of this email by return 
e-mail. The Company and its affiliates rule out any and every liability 
resulting from this or any other electronic transmission.

Date: December 2, 2025

Dear Sir/Madam,

I am writing to formally express my disappointment and concern regarding the delivery of my recent order (#653494142074617856), placed on November 29, 2025, for an amount of Rs. 1,372.77.

Today, December 2, 2025, the delivery person (who introduced himself as Mr. Vijay) not only delivered the order a day later than scheduled but also demanded Rs. 2,447 instead of the actual order value. To my shock, the invoice pasted on the parcel appeared tampered, with the amount to reflect sum.

This is not the first time I have faced issues with deliveries from PharmEasy. Last month, another order was wrongfully cancelled and displayed as "cancelled by the customer," which was entirely untrue. These repeated incidents point to a systemic issue in your delivery process, where customers are being misled and overcharged.

Such practices are unacceptable and erode trust in your platform. I request the following actions:

1. An immediate reaction to why the delivery person demanded an excess amount (Rs. 1,074).
2. A thorough investigation into the conduct of the delivery personnel and the tampering of invoices.
3. Assurance that such incidents will not recur.

For your kind information, I have enclosed the tampered payment receipt and invoice.
I expect a prompt resolution and a detailed response within 48 hours. Please feel free to contact me for any clarification.

I look forward to your prompt attention and action.

Sincerely,
Dr A. Nicholas Daniel
